text:
He who promotes #HumanRights must emphasize 5 basic rights before others:
1 right to live safely without being killed
2 right to have enough food
3 right to have basic medical care
4 right to be educated
5 right to have a job with an income
@mahbubani_k

text:
The #DigitalServicesTax issues highlight countries' conflicts over "digital sovereignty".
The US has a double standard on the issue, taking advantage of intl laws as a measurement of the DSTs' legitimacy, but unwilling to resolve the dispute via @WTO.

text: Today is #EinoLeinoDay in Finland, a day to celebrate poetry and summer. Finland announced the end to #COVID19 state of emergency not long ago, marking its achievement in fighting against the virus. It means people could finally start to resume normal life and enjoy the summer! https://t.co/Ty7X2vqvDv

Today is #WorldRainforestDay.
Preserving biodiversity, protecting wetlands, improving forest coverage, reducing soil pollution would all contribute to reducing the risk of disease emergence by restoring the buffer against epidemic diseases. @MartinVncnt
https://t.co/DbHkNkbJDP https://t.co/8SaHkIUdKI

When 20k masks donated by China’s Xiamen Airlines arrived in the Netherlands on March 18, a 73-year-old Dutch citizen wrote to Chinese embassy: "We are deeply moved that China is willing to help others while still struggling with its own fight. Thank you!"
